 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Recruiting Manager, Facebook Reality Labs Facebook 622 reviews Remote Remote Facebook 622 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. The Specialized Technology Recruiting Team at Facebook supports specialized technical hiring across unique hardware initiatives and innovative technologies. These organizations are responsible for developing and building the software and hardware platforms that power Facebook, its Infrastructure, and its family of apps today (including Data Center, Core Systems Engineering, Foundation, Enterprise, Network Engineering, Production Engineering, Connectivity, Privacy and Security teams) and the Facebook Reality Labs platform (Augmented and Virtual Reality and Artificial Intelligence [AI]).As we hire some of the best technical minds around, we need the best recruiting minds to match our business needs. As a Recruiting Manager, you will apply your operational depth and strategic thinking to develop, drive, and execute on the staffing strategies within our Optics (AR/VR) pillar. You will lead a team of staffing professionals who execute against global hiring targets and work closely with multiple stakeholders to drive world class recruiting practices with a constant eye on scaling for the future. In this role, you will know how to manage, mentor, and guide a team of managers, recruiters and/or sourcers through all facets of the recruiting life-cycle. 
Inspire, grow and nurture a team of recruiting professionals to deliver against Business hiring needs while meeting quality expectations 
Providing mentorship, guidance and career development to members of your team 
Collaborate with key business leadership partners to understand future plans and develop a global strategy to deliver on these plans 
Lead comprehensive top-down vision and recruitment strategy for Facebookâ€™s Optics AR/VR teams 
Leverage data analytics to drive operational improvements and amplify operational excellence to support team's rapid growth 
Partner with Facebook hiring managers to develop a detailed profile of target candidates with data-driven advice on the range of logical possibilities 
Define overall recruiting performance goals across the team 
Lead and develop recruiting managers to scale their teams 
Champion recruiting process improvements and recruiting tool enhancements on a global level 
Design and implement cutting-edge sourcing strategy for team and hiring managers 
Build effective working relationships with internal and external stakeholders and be recognized as trusted advisor in all recruitment matters 
Understand HR-related regulations and compliance procedures across North America, EMEA and APAC 
8+ years of recruiting experience 
4+ years of experience managing a team of recruiters and/or sourcers 
Experience managing teams of 10+ direct reports 
Experience designing and implementing global recruiting strategies 
Experience collaborating with key business leaders and senior cross-functional partners 
Experience translating data and analysis into strategic recruitment processes and recommendations 
Technical recruiting experience 
Experience managing technical recruiting teams 
Experience building and scaling technical recruitment teams 
Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we're just getting started. 
Facebook is proud to be an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, gender expression, transgender status, sexual stereotypes, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. Facebook is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for candidates with disabilities in our recruiting process. If you need any assistance or accommodations due to a disability, please let us know at accommodations-ext@fb.com. 
